Combine chicken, Rice-A-Roni Chicken & Broccoli, garlic, ginger, oyster sauce, sugar, and egg whites. Form twelve chicken meatballs. Heat a wide non-stick skillet, or flat-bottomed wok over medium heat. Brown "Lion's head" balls in vegetable and sesame oils. Add green onions, a slice of ginger, water and Special Seasoning, as directed on package. Cook 25 minutes. Add spinach and simmer until spinach has wilted and Lion's Heads are cooked through. Serve, garnished with sesame seeds, and optional cilantro.